Couture Africa on Saturday unveiled the Couture Africa Style Awards at Emara Ole Sereni Nairobi. The annual awards celebrate the best-dressed individuals in various industries alongside embracing fashion in Africa. Actress Catherine Kamau, alias Kate the Actress, bagged the Most Stylish Female Entertainer and topped the list as the Most Stylish Person of the Year. In sports, Eliud Kipchoge emerged as the Most Stylish Sportsman. Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho and Sports CS Amina Mohamed were awarded as the most stylish male and female public servants respectively. This yearâ€™s focus was on individuals who have a distinct, consistent and outstanding sense of style.